track.name: Good Morning Heartache
comments: Awww, Billie you hit me right in the heart with your pain and sorrow
this song makes me want to cry my eyes out
The friend that hides in my shadow. When I awake it greets me with...Good morning heartache...*
"... Start my days saying- good morning heartache, what's new?..."
Dang, Billie Holliday is dope. I wish I can go back into time and give her one of my beat CDs.
In those days they still had time to sing a song for their headaches in the morning. Today it's all rush and out to work before you're even awake. Just kidding, great song, great performance.
... but you are here to stay
This really personifies a heartache as a living being.  It sounds like she's looking right at him over a cup of coffee.
